public enum BurstCategory
extends java.lang.Enum<BurstCategory>

The BurstCategory Enumeration specifies constant values that describe the different categories of bursts that occur when data is transferred.

Enum Constant Detail

BURSTCAT_PROTOCOL

public static final BurstCategory BURSTCAT_PROTOCOL
A Protocol Burst. This is the default burst category. A Protocol burst consists of unwanted packets that are being transferred.

BURSTCAT_LOSS

public static final BurstCategory BURSTCAT_LOSS
A Loss burst. This burst consists of the packets that are lost while being transferred. It also includes the Recovered and Duplicate Burst types.

public static final BurstCategory BURSTCAT_USER

BURSTCAT_LONG

public static final BurstCategory BURSTCAT_LONG
A Long burst. A Long burst has a duration of more than 5 seconds, and typically transfers large amounts of data.

BURSTCAT_PERIODICAL

public static final BurstCategory BURSTCAT_PERIODICAL
A Periodical Burst. If the Internet Addresses, host names, or object names are the same for the packets in a set burst over a period of time, then those bursts are considered Periodical bursts.
